  "doc_id": "57102",
  "text": "We assign a prior polarity score to each word by using the scores provided by the Dictionary of Affect in Language (DAL) [CITATION_1] augmented with WordNet (Fellbaum, 1998) to improve coverage. We additionally augment it with Wiktionary, emoticon, and acronym dictionaries to improve coverage in social media [CITATION_2] . The DAL covers 50.1% of the vocabulary, 16.5% are proper nouns which we exclude due to their lack of polarity. WordNet covers 8.7% of the vocabulary and Wiktionary covers 12.5% of the vocabulary. Finally, 3.6% of the vocabulary are emoticons, acronyms, word lengthening, and forms of punctuation. 8.6% of the vocabulary is not covered which means we find a prior polarity for 96.4% of the vocabulary. In addition to these dictionaries we also use SentiWordNet [CITATION_3] as a new distinct feature that is used in addition to the prior polarity computed from the DAL scores.",
